author: cbc
title: 5 arrested on drug trafficking charges in Happy Valley-Goose Bay
text:
Police in Happy Valley-Goose Bay arrested five people on drug trafficking charges following the execution of a search warrant Thursday.
Officers with Happy Valley-Goose Bay RCMP, as well as a police dog, carried out the search on a property in the town and seized a quantity of cocaine, marijuana, prescription pills, drug paraphernalia, a firearm and a large sum of cash.
Two men, aged 47 and 43, and three women, 46, 36 and 21 were arrested. Police said all five were from the Happy Valley-Goose Bay area.
They are currently being held in custody and will appear in court.
The investigation is ongoing and anyone with information is asked to contact police or Crime Stoppers.
